Russia announced a unilateral ceasefire across Ukraine on May 9-10 for WWII Victory Day. The truce pauses hostilities in the year-long war, following Russian strikes yesterday that killed 10 people. Russia threatens retaliation against disruptions. Ukrainian President Zelensky reported drone hits on oil tankers yesterday.

In the Strait of Hormuz, U.S. Navy warships shot down missiles and drones targeting escorted ships, including UAE tankers. The UAE blamed Iran for the drone strike. India's foreign ministry condemned Iran over the UAE attack. Separately, an explosion at a fireworks plant in central China killed at least 26 people and injured others, state media reported. Search and rescue operations concluded, casualty verification continues, and Xi Jinping ordered a thorough probe. The WHO confirmed seven hantavirus cases, including three deaths, on the MV Hondius cruise ship off Cabo Verde. One British national is in intensive care among 147 passengers from 23 countries, including 17 Americans.

Narendra Modi's BJP won the West Bengal assembly elections after leading in nearly 200 seats during yesterday's vote count. An explosion killed nine workers in a Colombia coal mine despite weeks-earlier warnings from the national agency on gas buildup. Mali junta leader Assimi Goïta assumed defense minister duties after Sadio Camara's death in a suspected suicide bombing during attacks. Israeli settlers intensified attacks against Palestinians in the West Bank, as military officials called for government action."}
